__Mode de commercialisation envisagé :__

Notre commercialisation est aujourd’hui focalisée pour initier des projets pilotes / POCs avec des industriels dans les trois secteurs cibles :

- __COSMETIQUE \(\#1\) :__
	- Approche directe vers quelques grandes marques \(COTY, L’OREAL, CHANEL\), c’est\-à\-dire les donneurs d’ordre concernant l’usage avec les usagers et les consommateurs\.
		- COTY : RDV avec l’équipe Paris à COSMETICS/360 \(Paris\) et l’équipe HQ à CES \(Las Vegas\) et accord de progresser vers des pilotes use\-cases \(projets encore à être validés\)\.
		- L’OREAL : RDV avec l’équipe d’innovation à CES \(Las Vegas\)\. Rencontres en cours d’organisation\.
	- Approche des fabricants de formulation et essence \(MANE, FIRMENICH, ROBERTET\), donc plus tôt dans la chaine ce qui peut vouloir dire une distribution vers plusieurs clients prescripteurs\.
		- MANE et FIRMENICH : Rencontrées à FRAGRANCE SUMMIT \(Paris\) avec les équipes d’innovations et technologiques, et prise de RDV en cours\.
	- Contact avec des sous\-traitants des grandes marques, APTAR et FAREVA\.
		- APTAR : RDV avec l’équipe HQ ensemble avec CEA Grenoble et Saclay et maintenant en discussion avec le Head of innovation WW pour des use\-cases\.
- __PHARMACEUTIQUE \(\#2\):__
	- Actuellement nous menons une approche très ciblée vers deux entreprise, SERVIER et ASTRAZENECA\.
		- SERVIER : RDV en course d’organisation\.
- __COATING \(\#3\)__
	- Nous menons une action vers l’association nationale française des coatings et peintures AFTPVA\.
		- STIKOIA et CERINNOV : Des RDV et discussion avec ces deux spécialistes de colles industriels en cours\.

__Ressources clés pour l’entreprise :__

- Les trois co\-fondateurs\.
- Le financement du CTO et le R&D Director \(disponible 50% sur le projet\)\.
- Les ressources disponibles via le labo DTNM chez CEA Grenoble pour la pré\-industrialisation des marqueurs\.
- Le soutien contractuel de CEA Grenoble pour les premiers projets industriels bilatéraux pour confirmer le business model et la faisabilité industrielle comme phase avant la création de la société INOOCQ\.
- __Le caractère innovant de l’offre__

__En quoi votre offre est\-elle innovante ?__

__MARQUEUR :__

- Le marqueur d’INOOCQ est « biocompatible » et peut s’intégrer directement dans des médicaments et des produits cosmétiques \(crème, parfum,…\) comme une matière première sans impact sur les caractéristiques de ces produits
- Le marqueur d’INOOCQ peut également s’intégrer sur le packaging primaire ou secondaire via des marquages invisibles ou par exemple via l’encre d’écriture sur le produit ou le packaging\.

__DETECTION :__

- Détection non\-dédiée par un appareil portable type smartphone ou tablette\.

__CUSTOMISABLE :__

- Aux deux points précédents s’ajoutent une customisation pour rendre l’authentification entièrement unique par une corrélation entre détection et produit :
	- Par exemple, le marqueur « A » avec la densité « B » aura des corrélations différentes dans une crème de peau et un parfum, donc deux customisations différentes gérées par l’application mobile\.

__BREVET :__

- La solution identiDOTS, marqueurs \+ détection par smartphone, est brevetée\.

__A quel\(s\) besoin\(s\) répond votre innovation ?__

- Actuellement les trois secteurs ciblés n’arrivent pas à implémenter une solution qui permet aux usagers finaux \(cosmétique, pharmaceutique, couche/colle/peintures\) d’authentifier et valider un produit\.
- La solution INOOCQ rend cela possible dans différents niveaux dans les trois secteurs soit en remplaçant la solution existante ou en complément à une solution existante\.
- Les clients d’INOOCQ intègrent dans leurs propres solution mobiles la solution digitale d’identiDOTS\.
	- Cela permet à leurs utilisateurs d’authentifier et valider les produits en utilisant leurs smartphones\. Il est important à noter que cette authentification et validation se fait offline \(le smartphone n’a pas besoin d’être connecté\)\.
	- Cela permet également à communiquer sur ce sujet avec leurs utilisateurs\.

__Quelles sont les autres solutions actuellement utilisées ?__

__Quelles en sont leurs limites ?__

Les solutions concurrentes sont dans la plupart des cas plus sur l’axe de la traçabilité que l’authentification / validation des produits mêmes, et très orientées « QR\-code » \(hologramme, QR\-code spéciale, …\)\. Un QR\-code, même complexe, est dans la plupart des cas copiable\. Hormis ce challenge, une logistique plus ou moins manuelle est nécessaire, ce qui rend ces solutions compliquées et couteuses en handling\. Certaines solutions continuent à utiliser une détection dédiée, ce qui correspond aux limites identifiées il y a 4 ans\.

__Comment comptez\-vous valider ou avez\-vous validé que votre solution est pertinente pour vos clients / utilisateurs / bénéficiaires ?__

Le pivot effectué depuis 4 ans par notre CTO a donné la solution actuelle qui enlève les deux obstacles :

- Marqueurs non\-toxiques \(et « biocompatibles »\)
- Détection simple par smartphone \(ou tablette\)
- Le véritable changement que ce pivot crée un paradigm\-shift pour le marché : pouvoir avoir des marqueurs BIOCOMPATIBLES DANS UN PRODUIT OU LE PLUS PROCHE POSSIBLE DU PRODUIT AVEC UNE DETECTION PAR SMARTPHONE, MEME PAR UN CONSOMMATEUR \!

__Quels sont les facteurs clés de succès identifiés ?__

- Notre capacité à signer et valider les projets pilotes, d’abord bilatéraux avec le CEA Grenoble puis avec l’entité INOOCQ SAS \(multiples actions de prospection en cours\)\.
- L’industrialisation d’abord interne en petite quantité puis en externe pour une monté en volume \(processus actuellement initié\)\.
- Compléter le développement de la solution digitale incluant un « library » pour tablettes et smartphones\.
- Notre capacité à pénétrer les segments ciblés \(cosmétiques, pharma et coating\)\.

__Quels sont les facteurs de risques identifiés ?__

__Les risques technologiques sont :__

- L’industrialisation prend du retard par rapport aux engagements de projets pilotes avec des industriels\.
	- Pour éliminer ce risque il faut noter que nous avons déjà mise en place la possibilité de pré\-production avec les ressources disponibles au sein du CEA Grenoble\.
- Le développement de l’application mobile peut rencontrer des freins technologiques concernant la mesure avec les caméras des smartphones et tablettes\.
	- Pour diminuer \(et partiellement éliminer\) ce risque nous nous focalisons d’abord sur une mise en place avec l’écosystème d’Apple \(smartphone et tablette avec iOS\)\.
- Le life\-time des marqueurs\.
	- Le life\-time de nos marqueurs suffit pour les applications envisagées\. Toutefois nous avons besoin d’accélérer sur la phase de test afin de valider cet élément à travers les différents projets bilatéraux à venir\.

__Le risque du marché est :__

- Qu’aucun fabricant ne s’occupe du problème d’authentification pour les usagers finaux\.…
	- Les diverses réglementations dans les différents secteurs ciblés demandent de tracer les produits de la matière première au produit final… avec le challenge actuel de relier le produit même à une chaine logistique\. La solution d’INOOCQ rend possible de valider un produit à un niveau très bas dans la chaine de traçabilité\.

Ci\-joint quelques commentaires concernant la solution INOOCQ pour les différentes catégories de concurrence :

INOOCQ : Marqueurs intégrables dans les produits avec détection simple par appareil portable \(smartphone, tablette\) et probablement avec la partie marqueur moins couteux\.

CONCURRENCE DIRECTE

__Des solutions d’authentification non\-intrusive, type traitement d’une image prise avec une caméra\.__

INOOCQ : Les solutions existantes sont tributaires aux formes et aux surfaces des produits\. Les marqueurs d’INOOCQ sont entièrement dissociés aux formes ou surfaces des produits avec une détection simple et off\-line avec appareil portable \(smartphone, tablette\)\.

__Des solutions d’identification par caractérisation d’un produit \(par exemple la caractérisation du vin par une signature de la composition par un test d’échantillonnage\)\.__

INOOCQ : Les solutions existantes sont assez compliquées à mettre en œuvre et à détecter ou à caractériser\. Si les marqueurs d’INOOCQ sont utilisés à la place ils donneront une authentification simple du produit et cela off\-line appareil portable \(smartphone, tablette\)\.

CONCURRENCE INDIRECTE

__Des solutions de traçabilité, type QR\-code simple ou « intelligents », placé sur les produits ou sur le packaging des produits\.__

INOOCQ : Marqueurs intégrables dans les produits avec détection simple off\-line par appareil portable \(smartphone, tablette\) et la solution est intégrable dans la chaine de production des produits et non pas un ajout logistique, ce qui est un apport de simplicité fort\. Il est à noter que les systèmes type QR\-code apportent des informations sur les produits que n’apporte pas la solution d’INOOCQ, donc complémentaire pour rendre l’authentification pure plus simple\.

# <a id="_ongeptl2j49j"></a>Overview

## <a id="_4052czhcq4zw"></a>Context

#### <a id="_gz6om11e1dbu"></a>Company \(Inoocq\)

Inoocq introduces identiDOTS®, a groundbreaking anti\-counterfeiting technology\. This innovative solution addresses critical needs for security and traceability across sectors such as cosmetics, pharmaceuticals, and more\.

#### <a id="_prqt5zgxjyeq"></a>Team

Inoocq boasts an agile team dedicated to revolutionizing anti\-counterfeiting solutions:

- NORBERG Jahrl Stefan: Visionary leader guiding strategic direction\.
- Research and Development Experts: Innovators in marker technology\.
- Business Development Specialists: Forging partnerships and market growth\.
- Customer Support Team: Ensuring seamless implementation\.
- Strategic Advisors: Providing industry insights and guidance\.

#### <a id="_1kjcwwtai3qr"></a>Project \(identiDOTS® for Cosmetics\)

Inoocq's project aims to authenticate cosmetics with bioDOTS®, ensuring transparency, traceability, and consumer safety\. The goal is to establish identiDOTS® as the industry standard, empowering manufacturers with effective anti\-counterfeiting measures\.

## <a id="_by1gopij1xsj"></a>          Objectives \(Inoocq and identiDOTS®\)

The cosmetics industry is constantly evolving, characterized by a culture of innovation and change\. The growing demand for beauty and personal care products creates a favorable environment for the introduction of new solutions, such as those offered by INOOCQ\. Focusing specifically on this sector, INOOCQ aims to address an urgent need for counterfeit prevention and authenticity verification by providing manufacturers with advanced solutions such as identiDOTS®\.

Furthermore, INOOCQ operates not only in the cosmetics industry but also in the pharmaceutical and coating sectors\. Leveraging its expertise and technology, INOOCQ extends its solutions to address similar challenges faced by manufacturers in these industries\.

With this in mind, INOOCQ seeks to develop and implement a robust economic model and a tailored Go\-To\-Market strategy for the cosmetics industry\. This entails designing a B2B business model and revenue structure incorporating INOOCQ's SIGNATURE \(biocompatible markers\) and DIGITAL \(smartphone detection\) technologies\. The primary objective is to establish a scalable and effective strategy for material sourcing, subcontractor partnerships, distribution networks, and end\-user engagement within the coating sector\. The ultimate goal is to ensure widespread adoption and commercial success of identiDOTS®, thereby offering manufacturers cutting\-edge anti\-counterfeiting solutions in the cosmetics industry\.

# <a id="_8107bw1ec38n"></a>Choice of the Topic

The cosmetics industry presents itself as a dynamic sector full of potential and complexities, ripe for innovative disruption\. INOOCQ, with its pioneering solutions in counterfeit prevention and authenticity verification, is well\-positioned to make a substantial impact within this dynamic landscape\. By delving into the wealth of data available, it's evident that INOOCQ's entry into the cosmetics market is not just a viable choice but a strategic imperative\.

First and foremost, the sheer scale of the global cosmetics market beckons to INOOCQ\. With figures surpassing $200 billion in 2020 and continuous growth, the market represents an attractive opportunity for growth and expansion\. By 2031, the global cosmetics market will weigh $200 billion more than it does today<a id="footnote-ref-0"></a>[\[1\]](#footnote-0)\. This upward trajectory is fueled by a growing demand for beauty and personal care products, underscoring a rising demand that INOOCQ can readily capitalize on\.

![](data:image/png;base64,)

[Cosmetics Market 2020\-2030](https://exactitudeconsultancy.com/fr/reports/36137/cosmetics-market/)

Moreover, by dissecting the market into distinct regions, INOOCQ can effectively tailor its approach\. The United States \(24%\), Europe \(31%\), and China \(20%\) represent some of the largest cosmetics markets in the world, offering substantial penetration opportunities for INOOCQ's solutions\. These regions also present specific needs for cosmetic product authenticity verification, thus creating market niches for INOOCQ to exploit\.

We have chosen to primarily focus on the __haircare__ sector due to its significance within the cosmetics industry\. In __2024__, this market was valued at approximately__ $90,59 billion __and is expected to* continue growing significantly* in the years to come<a id="footnote-ref-1"></a>[\[2\]](#footnote-1)\. The United States, Europe, and China are among the leading countries in this field, with well\-established brands such as Pantene, Head & Shoulders, L'Oréal, and Rejoice\.

We have identified four customer segments in the luxury sector, namely: customer segmentation in the haircare sector, customer sub\-segmentation for luxury brands, high\-end salon brands, and international luxury conglomerates\. This approach allows INOOCQ to effectively address the specific needs of each segment, thus reinforcing its position as a trusted leader in the luxury cosmetics and haircare industry\. Haircare customer segmentation involves identifying different types of consumers in this sector, taking into account their needs, preferences, and purchasing habits\. INOOCQ can thus offer personalized solutions, ranging from product authenticity verification to counterfeit prevention\.

Understanding the various levels of luxury sought by consumers is crucial\. Customer sub\-segmentation for luxury brands addresses this issue specifically\. By providing tailored solutions for each sub\-segment, INOOCQ becomes a preferred ally for brands that prioritize preserving their reputation and integrity\.

High\-end salon brands attract discerning clientele due to their reputation and expertise\. By offering solutions tailored to their needs for authenticity verification and counterfeit prevention, INOOCQ strengthens its presence in this lucrative market\.

International luxury conglomerates own a portfolio of renowned brands in various sectors, including haircare\. By offering global solutions for authenticity verification and counterfeiting prevention, INOOCQ becomes a crucial partner for these major players in the luxury industry\.

The continued growth of the sector is driven by *increasing demand for quality products*, particularly in developing countries where interest in beauty and personal care products is on the rise\. Additionally, luxury haircare products are thriving, with a growing demand for high\-end products that offer superior results and a quality experience\.

Consumers are now seeking products tailored to their specific needs, and cultural and social trends also influence the market\. The "natural hair" movement is a perfect example, as it has stimulated demand for products tailored to natural hair, prompting many brands to develop specific ranges to meet this demand\.

Furthermore, *sustainability* has become a key factor in the haircare sector\. Consumers are increasingly concerned about sustainability and ethics, seeking out brands committed to sustainable practices such as the use of environmentally friendly ingredients, recyclable packaging, and ethical manufacturing practices\.

INOOCQ's innovative solutions address the pressing needs of various stakeholders within the cosmetics industry ecosystem\. From beauty product manufacturers and distributors to retailers and end consumers, the demand for authenticity verification and counterfeit prevention is palpable\. With the proliferation of counterfeit and fake products in the cosmetics and haircare market, the industry has an urgent need for robust solutions, and INOOCQ stands at the forefront to meet this demand\.

Furthermore, the *ever\-evolving landscape of the cosmetics and haircare industry*, characterized by emerging product and consumption trends, presents both challenges and opportunities\. INOOCQ's agility and adaptability are essential for navigating these complexities and seizing emerging opportunities while effectively managing associated risks\.

In conclusion, the convergence of market dynamics, technological advancements, and INOOCQ's innovative solutions presents a unique opportunity for the company to establish itself in the cosmetics and haircare market\. By strategically targeting specific regions and customer segments, INOOCQ can harness the vast potential of the global cosmetics and *haircare market*, thereby *establishing its position as a trusted leader and reshaping the industry landscape in the process\.*

# <a id="_t8viqd5vcfku"></a>Business Model

## <a id="_on0gtv4ov5p"></a>Customer Segments

### <a id="_3ikndcng43i6"></a>Customer Sub\-segmentation for Luxury Brands

#### <a id="_ar4f90ct0w72"></a>Established Prestige Brands:

- __Heritage Brands__: These are luxury haircare brands with a rich heritage and history in the industry, often dating back several decades\. They leverage their legacy, expertise, and iconic products to maintain a loyal customer base and uphold their reputation for quality and innovation\.
- __Exclusive Formulations__: Established prestige brands are known for their proprietary formulations, incorporating advanced technologies, rare botanical extracts, and luxury ingredients sourced from around the world\. They invest heavily in research and development to continuously innovate and elevate the efficacy of their products\.
- __Global Presence__: These brands have a strong global presence, with distribution channels spanning luxury department stores, high\-end salons, specialty boutiques, and e\-commerce platforms\. They often engage in strategic marketing initiatives, brand collaborations, and experiential events to maintain visibility and desirability among affluent consumers\.

__Example → *Kérastase \(L'Oréal Professional\)*__*: With a heritage dating back to 1964, Kérastase is renowned for its luxurious haircare products developed with advanced technology and tailored solutions for various hair types and concerns\. Their iconic ranges include the Chronologiste, Elixir Ultime, and Resistance collections\.*

#### <a id="_27wzot5m34sd"></a>Boutique Luxury Brands:

- __Artisanal Craftsmanship__: Boutique luxury haircare brands pride themselves on artisanal craftsmanship, small\-batch production, and attention to detail\. They emphasize handcrafted formulations, meticulous blending techniques, and limited edition releases to create a sense of exclusivity and rarity\.
- __Personalized Experience__: These brands offer a personalized shopping experience, often through boutique stores, luxury spas, or online platforms, where customers receive expert advice, tailored recommendations, and VIP treatment\. They foster strong relationships with their clientele, nurturing a sense of community and loyalty\.
- __Aesthetic Branding__: Boutique luxury brands place a premium on aesthetic branding, with sleek, minimalist packaging designs, luxurious textures, and sensory experiences\. They appeal to consumers who appreciate the intersection of beauty, art, and design, elevating the haircare ritual into a sensory indulgence\.

__Example *→ R\+Co*__*: Founded by a collective of renowned hair stylists, R\+Co offers a range of high\-end haircare products characterized by artistry, craftsmanship, and unique formulations\. Their products, such as the Television Perfect Hair Shampoo and High Dive Moisture and Shine Cream, are known for their artistic packaging and premium ingredients\.*

#### <a id="_g2nxibcfhp2a"></a>High\-End Salon Brands:

- __Professional Endorsements__: High\-end salon brands collaborate closely with celebrity hairstylists, top salons, and industry professionals to develop and endorse their product ranges\. They draw inspiration from salon trends, techniques, and customer feedback to create salon\-quality products tailored for at\-home use\.
- __Performance\-driven Solutions__: These brands prioritize performance\-driven formulations, backed by scientific research, clinical testing, and professional endorsements\. They address specific hair concerns such as damage repair, color preservation, frizz control, and scalp health, delivering visible results and salon\-worthy finishes\.
- __Education and Training__: High\-end salon brands invest in education and training programs for hairstylists, providing them with product knowledge, styling techniques, and business support\. They foster a sense of community and expertise within the salon industry, positioning themselves as trusted partners for professionals and consumers alike\.

__Example *→ Bumble and bumble*__* *__*\(Estée Lauder Companies\)*__*: Founded as a New York City salon, Bumble and bumble has grown into a global brand known for its professional\-grade haircare products and styling innovations\. Their products, such as the Hairdresser's Invisible Oil and Thickening Spray, are trusted by hairstylists and consumers alike for their performance and versatility\.*

#### <a id="_pgjhccqg7w61"></a>International Luxury Conglomerates:

- __Diverse Portfolio__: International luxury conglomerates operate diverse portfolios of haircare brands, ranging from mass\-market to ultra\-prestige segments\. They leverage economies of scale, global distribution networks, and cross\-brand synergies to drive growth and profitability across their brand portfolio\.
- __Innovation Centers__: These conglomerates often have dedicated research and innovation centers focused on haircare science, technology, and trends\. They collaborate with academic institutions, industry experts, and beauty influencers to drive innovation and stay at the forefront of product development\.
- __Brand Architecture__: International luxury conglomerates employ strategic brand architecture to position their haircare brands within distinct market segments, catering to different consumer preferences, price points, and distribution channels\. They carefully manage brand identities, messaging, and positioning to maximize market share and brand equity\.

__Example *→ Aveda \(Estée Lauder Companies\)*__*: Aveda, a subsidiary of the Estée Lauder Companies, is a global leader in natural and sustainable beauty products\. Known for its plant\-based formulations and commitment to environmental responsibility, Aveda offers a range of premium haircare products, including the Damage Remedy and Be Curly collections\.*

__Example *→ L'Oréal Professional*__*: As part of the L'Oréal Group, L'Oréal Professional encompasses a diverse portfolio of luxury haircare brands tailored for professional use\. Brands like Redken and Pureology offer salon\-quality products, advanced treatments, and personalized solutions for haircare professionals and consumers worldwide\.*

## <a id="_49jr4v1dz1sv"></a>Value Proposition

The solution provided by INOOCQ’s identiDOTS® technology would generate the most gains and remove the most pain for market segments that are highly susceptible to counterfeiting and where the authenticity of products is critical\. Considering the 4 sub\-segments within the premium and luxury haircare market, __Boutique Luxury Brands__ could be a prime candidate\. These brands often emphasize exclusivity, artisanal quality, and a personalized customer experience\. The personalized nature of their products means that authenticity is paramount to maintaining their brand image and customer loyalty\. These are areas where INOOCQ’s identiDOTS® biomarker solution can provide considerable value\.

The solution can offer significant gains for __Boutique Luxury Brands__ by enhancing the exclusivity and perceived artisanal value of their products through verifiable authenticity, strengthening customer loyalty by ensuring they receive genuine, high\-quality products, and supporting the brand’s narrative of artisanal quality and attention to detail with advanced anti\-counterfeiting measures\.

Simultaneously, it can alleviate substantial pains by protecting the brand’s reputation and the integrity of their artisanal products from being diluted by counterfeits, maintaining the trust of a niche customer base that values authenticity and craftsmanship, and reducing the risk of financial losses associated with counterfeit products infiltrating the market\.

In addition, __Established Prestige Brands__ may also stand to benefit considerably from INOOQC’s solution\. With a rich heritage and a reputation for quality, these brands stand to lose a lot from counterfeiting\. INOOCQ’s technology can help reinforce heritage and authority in the market by ensuring product authenticity and exclusivity of proprietary formulations, as well as shield reputation and market position from being undermined by counterfeit products, thus preserving their market position and customer trust\.

The other two segments, __High\-End Salon Brands__ and __International Luxury Conglomerates__, while they would also benefit from anti\-counterfeiting measures, may not see as much relative gain\. This is because conglomerates often have the resources to invest in their comprehensive anti\-counterfeiting systems, and professional endorsements may not rely as heavily on product authentication at the consumer level\.

By focusing more on boutique brands, INOOCQ can leverage its unique selling proposition of sophisticated, hard\-to\-replicate biomarker technology to meet the specific needs of boutique brands, which often lack the resources of larger conglomerates to implement complex anti\-counterfeiting measures\. This alignment between INOOCQ’s offerings and the boutique brands’ requirements could lead to a mutually beneficial partnership, making them an ideal potential client\.

## <a id="_6pc3okd8i2a6"></a>Pricing Strategy

Design a flexible pricing model that accounts for the varying needs and budgets of Boutique Luxury Brands\. Consider factors such as *brand size, product volume, customization requirements, *and the *perceived value of comprehensive authentication solutions*\. Inoocq's pricing strategy for identiDOTS must align with the varying needs and budgets of Boutique Luxury Brands while reflecting the value proposition of the two products: *packaging authentication* and *formula authentication*\. Here's a detailed breakdown of how Inoocq can design a flexible pricing model considering the main criteria:

#### <a id="_psp50c6z8lc0"></a>Packaging Authentication:

- __Base Pricing__: Offer a base price for the packaging authentication product, which provides standard authentication features suitable for most Boutique Luxury Brands\.
- __Tiered Pricing__: Introduce tiered pricing options based on brand size and product volume\. Smaller boutique brands with lower product volumes may opt for a basic package at a lower price point, while larger luxury conglomerates with higher product volumes may choose premium packages with additional features or customization\.
- __Customization__: Offer customization options such as branding integration, unique marker configurations, and tailored authentication processes\. Price these customizations as add\-on services, allowing brands to choose the level of customization based on their specific requirements\.
- __Volume Discounts__: Provide volume discounts for brands committing to larger quantities of packaging authentication markers\. This incentivizes bulk purchases and encourages long\-term partnerships\.
- __Subscription Model__: Consider offering a subscription\-based pricing model, where brands pay a recurring fee for ongoing access to identiDOTS authentication services\. This can include regular updates, maintenance, and customer support\.

#### <a id="_1ptsf15mp266"></a>Formula Authentication:

- __Research and Development Fee__: Since formula authentication requires extensive research and development efforts tailored to each partner Boutique Luxury Brand, charge an upfront fee to cover these costs\. This fee can vary based on the complexity of the formula, the level of customization required, and the duration of the R&D process\.
- __Performance\-Based Pricing__: Offer performance\-based pricing options tied to the effectiveness of the formula authentication solution\. Brands may be willing to pay higher fees if the identiDOTS technology leads to tangible benefits such as reduced counterfeiting, improved product integrity, or enhanced consumer trust\.
- __Long\-Term Contracts__: Encourage partners to commit to long\-term contracts for formula authentication services by offering discounted rates or bundled packages\. This provides stability for both parties and ensures a steady stream of revenue for Inoocq\.

#### <a id="_4sbklnx3u27b"></a>Flexibility and Customization:

- __Tailored Solutions__: Work closely with each Boutique Luxury Brand to understand their specific needs and preferences\. Offer customized pricing packages that address their unique requirements, ensuring a perfect fit for their budget and objectives\.
- __Negotiation__: Maintain flexibility in pricing negotiations, allowing room for adjustments based on factors such as brand loyalty, strategic partnerships, or mutually beneficial agreements\. Consider offering discounts, incentives, or value\-added services to secure deals with high\-value clients\.
- __Transparency__: Ensure transparency in pricing by clearly communicating the breakdown of costs, fees, and value\-added services included in each pricing package\. Provide detailed quotes and proposals outlining the pricing structure and terms of engagement to avoid misunderstandings and build trust with clients\.

## <a id="_q85769g91c1x"></a>Estimated Revenue for the end on 2025

This is an estimated calculation of the revenue generated from the clients with the RED and GREEN package options at the end of 2025 based on the pricing details provided earlier, considering that 8 of them are RED package clients and 2 of them are GREEN package clients\.

- 8 clients with the RED Package option
- 2 clients with the GREEN Package option

We'll need to use the pricing details provided earlier to calculate the estimated revenue:

__RED Package:__

General Entry Fee: €150,000 \- €200,000

Customization and R&D Costs: €100,000 \- €150,000

Tiered Pricing \(additional\): €30,000 \- €50,000

For simplicity, let's take the midpoint of the pricing range for each component:

General Entry Fee: €175,000

Customization and R&D Costs: €125,000

Tiered Pricing \(additional\): €40,000

Total cost per RED package: €175,000 \+ €125,000 \+ €40,000 = __€340,000__

__GREEN Package:__

General Entry Fee: €40,000 \- €60,000

Customization Add\-Ons: €5,000 \- €10,000

For simplicity, let's take the midpoint of the pricing range for each component:

General Entry Fee: €50,000

Customization Add\-Ons: €7,500

Total cost per GREEN package: €50,000 \+ €7,500 = __€57,500__

Now, let's calculate the estimated revenue:

Revenue from 8 RED packages: 8 \* €340,000 = €2,720,000

Revenue from 2 GREEN packages: 2 \* €57,500 = €115,000

Total estimated revenue for Inoocq: €2,720,000 \+ €115,000 = __€2,835,000__

Therefore, the estimated revenue for Inoocq at the __end of 2025__, based on 8 clients with the RED package option and 2 clients with the GREEN package option, is €2,835,000\.

Considering this calculation, it is possible to estimate a revenue generation of 21% quarterly increase \(about __30% annual growth__\)\.
